<node id="&quot;HOMEOSTASIS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Homeostasis is a concept introduced by Cannon, referring to the maintenance of stable internal conditions in the body despite external changes."&lt;SEP&gt;"Homeostasis is a fundamental concept in physiology and biology, regulating various physiological processes such as digestion, thirst, hunger, fear, pain, shock, and the nervous and endocrine systems."&lt;SEP&gt;"Homeostasis is the maintenance of a stable internal environment in the body, which is crucial for survival and involves various physiological mechanisms to regulate blood sugar levels."&lt;SEP&gt;"Homeostasis is the state of maintaining internal conditions within narrow ranges."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-11676ae8259d9bef41b4ab8ba19335b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b7d9d5fbedb55c3eb193d14294704df3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-529cfcb3c05c829427368393e6f20532&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-06b4a9642d883a25a7c071da2debc224</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 34}]</data>
</node>
