  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Conditions set forth in Section 8.2 are specific requirements that must be met on the Effective Date."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0a7f06cdfef313832757561409e1f2e2</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TWENTY (20) BUSINESS DAYS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Twenty (20) Business Days is the time frame given to cure breaches before penalties apply."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0a7f06cdfef313832757561409e1f2e2</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TWENTY-FIVE (25) CALENDAR DAYS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Twenty-five (25) Calendar Days is the time frame given to address legal judgments or orders."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0a7f06cdfef313832757561409e1f2e2</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COURT OF COMPETENT JURISDICTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Court of Competent Jurisdiction is a legal body that has the authority to make judgments on the agreement."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0a7f06cdfef313832757561409e1f2e2</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GOVERNMENTAL AUTHORITY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Governmental Authority includes regulatory bodies that can issue judgments or orders on the agreement."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0a7f06cdfef313832757561409e1f2e2</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;REGULATORY AUTHORITY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Regulatory Authority is a specific type of governmental authority that can issue judgments or orders on the agreement."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0a7f06cdfef313832757561409e1f2e2</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CONSUMMATION OF A MATERIAL PORTION OF THE RESTRUCTURING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Consummation of a Material Portion of the Restructuring is a specific phase of the restructuring process that is subject to conditions and judgments."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0a7f06cdfef313832757561409e1f2e2</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NOTICE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Notice is a formal communication required for certain actions or events to take effect."&lt;SEP&gt;"Notice is a formal communication that triggers certain actions, such as providing extensions or terminating the agreement."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0a7f06cdfef313832757561409e1f2e2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-272024f9438dbb1eb8f8eb69b27c343b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 5}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 49}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 104}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DEERFIELD&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Deerfield is an organization that must hold or control a specific percentage of the Prepetition Agreement Claims during the Effective Period."&lt;SEP&gt;"Deerfield is an organization that must hold or control a specific percentage of the aggregate principal amount of the Prepetition Agreement Claims during the Effective Period."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-272024f9438dbb1eb8f8eb69b27c343b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 5}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 52}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BANKRUPTCY COURT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Bankruptcy Court is the court responsible for approving claims and managing the bankruptcy proceedings."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bankruptcy Court is the judicial body that oversees the calendar and any motions or pleadings related to the agreement."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-272024f9438dbb1eb8f8eb69b27c343b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d49561091ac27f1b0af51d94fd414636</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 5}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 49}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 104}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;OUTSIDE DATE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Outside Date is a deadline after which the agreement can be terminated by any party with written notice."&lt;SEP&gt;"Outside Date is a specific date by which the Plan must become effective, otherwise the Agreement can be terminated."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cdb728c5607b739e3d11672aa83be4ce&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-272024f9438dbb1eb8f8eb69b27c343b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 5}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 52}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MILESTONES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Milestones are significant points or achievements in a project or research that trigger certain payments or actions."&lt;SEP&gt;"Milestones are specific points in time or events that must be achieved, and the Supporting Lenders must provide extensions to accommodate the Bankruptcy Court’s calendar."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-272024f9438dbb1eb8f8eb69b27c343b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac8810aa347bb9046a5ebb7bb3c8da29</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 5}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 52}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TERMINATION EVENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Termination Event is an event that can cause the automatic termination of the agreement, such as the failure to hold or control the required percentage of claims or the filing of inconsistent motions."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-272024f9438dbb1eb8f8eb69b27c343b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 5}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 52}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;JUDGMENT OR ORDER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LEGAL_DOCUMENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Judgment or Order is a legal document that can affect the status of the stay and trigger a Termination Event."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-272024f9438dbb1eb8f8eb69b27c343b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 5}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 52}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BANKRUPTCY PROCEEDINGS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Bankruptcy Proceedings are the legal processes related to the Bankruptcy Court, which can affect the timeline and milestones."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-272024f9438dbb1eb8f8eb69b27c343b</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 5}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 52}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PETITION DATE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Petition Date is a specific date mentioned in the context of a legal proceeding or agreement."&lt;SEP&gt;"Petition Date is the date on which the company initiates bankruptcy proceedings under Chapter 11."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ec30e257221e71c474d6266d0784c302&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cdb728c5607b739e3d11672aa83be4ce</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 10}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 67}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 122}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PARTIES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Parties refer to the entities involved in the agreement, which are defined to complete the negotiation of terms and actions for restructuring."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a1d32997fcb863bfc733f7d28f71ab5d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;AFFILIATE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Affiliate is a concept referring to any other person that controls, is controlled by, or is under common control with a given person."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a1d32997fcb863bfc733f7d28f71ab5d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ALTERNATIVE TRANSACTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Alternative Transaction includes various business actions such as refinancing, recapitalization, share exchanges, and equity investments, except for ordinary course of business activities."&lt;SEP&gt;"Alternative Transaction is a type of transaction that includes alternative refinancing, recapitalization, share exchange, rights offering, equity investment, or other transactions."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a1d32997fcb863bfc733f7d28f71ab5d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e11945e8bccbcbdf01a6cf255f63a96</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 41}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 102}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NEGOTIATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Negotiation refers to the process of discussing and agreeing on the terms of the documents."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a1d32997fcb863bfc733f7d28f71ab5d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DOCUMENTS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Documents are the written agreements and terms that need to be negotiated and completed."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a1d32997fcb863bfc733f7d28f71ab5d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ACTIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Actions refer to the specific tasks or steps that need to be completed to effect the Restructuring."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a1d32997fcb863bfc733f7d28f71ab5d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PROMISES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Promises are the commitments made by the Parties in the Agreement."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a1d32997fcb863bfc733f7d28f71ab5d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CONSIDERATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Consideration refers to the value exchanged between the Parties, which is the promises and mutual covenants and agreements."&lt;SEP&gt;"Consideration refers to the value or payment involved in the Material Contracts, specifically more than $250,000 in the next 12 months."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a1d32997fcb863bfc733f7d28f71ab5d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-72a8869b8a35f37ec389834d0871ab40</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 5}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 58}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 113}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PREAMBLE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"DOCUMENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Preamble is a part of the Agreement that provides an overview or context for the document."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a1d32997fcb863bfc733f7d28f71ab5d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EXHIBITS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Exhibits are additional documents or materials referenced in the Agreement."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a1d32997fcb863bfc733f7d28f71ab5d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ANNEXES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Annexes are additional documents or materials referenced in the Agreement."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a1d32997fcb863bfc733f7d28f71ab5d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SCHEDULES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Schedules are additional documents or materials referenced in the Agreement."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a1d32997fcb863bfc733f7d28f71ab5d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;REORGANIZATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Reorganization refers to the process of restructuring the business or organization."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a1d32997fcb863bfc733f7d28f71ab5d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FINANCING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Financing refers to the process of obtaining funds for the reorganization."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a1d32997fcb863bfc733f7d28f71ab5d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;REFINANCING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Refinancing refers to the process of restructuring existing debt."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a1d32997fcb863bfc733f7d28f71ab5d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RECAPITALIZATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Recapitalization refers to the process of changing the capital structure of a company."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a1d32997fcb863bfc733f7d28f71ab5d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SHARE EXCHANGE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Share Exchange is the swapping of shares between companies, often as part of a larger restructuring or reorganization."&lt;SEP&gt;"Share Exchange refers to the process of exchanging shares for other assets or securities."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a1d32997fcb863bfc733f7d28f71ab5d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e11945e8bccbcbdf01a6cf255f63a96</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 41}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 103}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RIGHTS OFFERING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Rights Offering is the distribution of subscription rights to existing shareholders, allowing them to purchase additional shares at a discount."&lt;SEP&gt;"Rights Offering refers to the process of offering rights to existing shareholders to subscribe for new shares."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a1d32997fcb863bfc733f7d28f71ab5d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e11945e8bccbcbdf01a6cf255f63a96</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 41}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 103}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EQUITY INVESTMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Equity Investment is the act of investing in a company by purchasing its equity, often as part of a restructuring or reorganization."&lt;SEP&gt;"Equity Investment refers to the process of investing in the company through the purchase of equity."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a1d32997fcb863bfc733f7d28f71ab5d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e11945e8bccbcbdf01a6cf255f63a96</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 41}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 103}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PURCHASE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Purchase refers to the acquisition of assets or businesses, often involving the acquisition or disposition of assets or capital stock."&lt;SEP&gt;"Purchase refers to the act of buying assets or shares."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a1d32997fcb863bfc733f7d28f71ab5d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a6f0c8b641c5362496d9135cd0b32820</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 44}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SALE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Sale refers to the act of selling assets or shares."&lt;SEP&gt;"Sale refers to the transfer of ownership of assets or businesses, often involving the acquisition or disposition of assets or capital stock."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a1d32997fcb863bfc733f7d28f71ab5d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a6f0c8b641c5362496d9135cd0b32820</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 44}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DEBTOR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Debtor refers to the entity undergoing restructuring, including alternative transactions, equity issuances, and other significant business actions."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8e11945e8bccbcbdf01a6cf255f63a96</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 41}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 103}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ANTITRUST LAWS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Antitrust Laws are legal frameworks designed to prevent monopolization, restrain trade, or lessen competition through mergers or acquisitions."&lt;SEP&gt;"Antitrust Laws refer to laws designed to prohibit monopolies and promote fair competition at various governmental levels."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ec30e257221e71c474d6266d0784c302&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e11945e8bccbcbdf01a6cf255f63a96</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 41}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 102}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ANNEXES AND SCHEDULES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"DOCUMENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Annexes and Schedules are additional documents or schedules attached to the main document, providing further details or references."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8e11945e8bccbcbdf01a6cf255f63a96</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 41}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 103}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SALE OF ASSETS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Sale of Assets refers to the disposal of a significant portion of a Debtor's business or assets, except in the ordinary course of business."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8e11945e8bccbcbdf01a6cf255f63a96</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 41}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 103}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MERGER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Merger is a business combination where two or more companies join together to form a single entity."&lt;SEP&gt;"Merger is the combination of two or more companies into a single entity, which can be regulated by antitrust laws."&lt;SEP&gt;"Merger refers to the combination of two companies into one, often involving the acquisition or disposition of assets or capital stock."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a6f0c8b641c5362496d9135cd0b32820&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ec30e257221e71c474d6266d0784c302&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e11945e8bccbcbdf01a6cf255f63a96</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 44}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ACQUISITION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Acquisition is the process of one company gaining control of another, which can be regulated by antitrust laws."&lt;SEP&gt;"Acquisition is the process of purchasing another company or its assets, often resulting in a business combination."&lt;SEP&gt;"Acquisition refers to the process of purchasing assets or businesses outside the ordinary course of business, typically involving expenditures over $250,000."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a6f0c8b641c5362496d9135cd0b32820&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ec30e257221e71c474d6266d0784c302&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e11945e8bccbcbdf01a6cf255f63a96</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 42}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CONSOLIDATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Consolidation is a business combination where two or more companies merge into a single entity, often involving the transfer of assets and liabilities."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8e11945e8bccbcbdf01a6cf255f63a96</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 41}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 103}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EQUITY INTEREST&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Equity Interest refers to ownership stakes in a company, including securities or instruments convertible into equity."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8e11945e8bccbcbdf01a6cf255f63a96</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 41}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 103}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SUPRANATIONAL ANTITRUST LAW&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LAW"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Supranational Antitrust Law refers to antitrust regulations that apply across multiple countries or regions."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8e11945e8bccbcbdf01a6cf255f63a96</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 41}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 102}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NATIONAL ANTITRUST LAW&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LAW"</data>
  <data key="d1">"National Antitrust Law refers to antitrust regulations that apply within a specific country."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8e11945e8bccbcbdf01a6cf255f63a96</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 41}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 102}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FEDERAL ANTITRUST LAW&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LAW"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Federal Antitrust Law refers to antitrust regulations that apply at the federal level within a country."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8e11945e8bccbcbdf01a6cf255f63a96</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 41}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 102}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;STATE ANTITRUST LAW&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LAW"</data>
  <data key="d1">"State Antitrust Law refers to antitrust regulations that apply at the state level within a country."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8e11945e8bccbcbdf01a6cf255f63a96</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 41}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 102}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COUNTY ANTITRUST LAW&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LAW"</data>
  <data key="d1">"County Antitrust Law refers to antitrust regulations that apply at the county level within a country."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8e11945e8bccbcbdf01a6cf255f63a96</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 41}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 102}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LOCAL ANTITRUST LAW&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LAW"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Local Antitrust Law refers to antitrust regulations that apply at the local level within a country."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8e11945e8bccbcbdf01a6cf255f63a96</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 41}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 102}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DEBTORS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Debtors are the parties to whom the Company or its Subsidiaries owe money or have some form of financial obligation."&lt;SEP&gt;"Debtors refers to the parties who owe money and are seeking a reduction in their outstanding indebtedness."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ec30e257221e71c474d6266d0784c302&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-32603276a52db27e454f08ff7a05e930</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 5}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 56}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HSR ACT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LAW"</data>
  <data key="d1">"HSR Act is a specific piece of legislation that falls under antitrust laws, requiring notification and waiting periods for certain mergers and acquisitions."&lt;SEP&gt;"HSR Act refers to the Hart-Scott-Rodino Antitrust Improvements Act of 1976, as amended, which is a federal law regulating mergers and acquisitions."&lt;SEP&gt;"HSR Act refers to the Hart-Scott-Rodino Antitrust Improvements Act of 1976, as amended, which is a federal law regulating mergers and acquisitions.")</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5d607382550315031dd4556c77e174e0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ec30e257221e71c474d6266d0784c302</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 5}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 51}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SHERMAN ACT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LAW"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Sherman Act is a foundational U.S. antitrust law aimed at preventing monopolies and promoting fair competition."</data>
