<node id="&quot;NUCLEUS HIVE (NUC)&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A Nucleus Hive, or nuc, is a small but complete colony typically purchased locally and used as a starter unit for beekeeping. It includes frames, comb, brood, adult bees, and a new, young queen."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-eec9462a5adf7ec8d10f626e103389f3</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 16}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 86}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NEW BEEKEEPER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A New Beekeeper is someone who is starting to learn and practice beekeeping, often purchasing a nuc to begin their colony."&lt;SEP&gt;"New Beekeeper refers to someone who is just beginning to learn about beekeeping and managing colonies."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6e8e292472440147bfd5caa5df68f872&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eec9462a5adf7ec8d10f626e103389f3</data>
