</node>
<node id="&quot;ESTABLISHED HIVE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"An Established Hive is a well-established bee colony from which a Nucleus Hive (nuc) is drawn, providing a source of bees, frames, comb, brood, and a queen."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-eec9462a5adf7ec8d10f626e103389f3</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 16}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 86}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;THROW-AWAY BOX&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A Throw-Away Box is a temporary housing solution for a Nucleus Hive (nuc) before it is transferred to a permanent hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-eec9462a5adf7ec8d10f626e103389f3</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 16}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 86}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RETURNABLE BOX&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A Returnable Box is a reusable container for transporting a Nucleus Hive (nuc) to its new home."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-eec9462a5adf7ec8d10f626e103389f3</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 16}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 86}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SINGLE-STORY HIVE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A Single-Story Hive is a type of hive structure that a new beekeeper might use to accept and transport a Nucleus Hive (nuc)."&lt;SEP&gt;"Single-story Hive is a structure designed to house a bee colony, providing a specific environment for the bees to live and produce honey."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6e8e292472440147bfd5caa5df68f872&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eec9462a5adf7ec8d10f626e103389f3</data>
