</node>
<node id="&quot;PACKAGE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A Package is a component of a Nucleus Hive (nuc) that is installed in the hive before the colony is fully accepted by the existing bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-eec9462a5adf7ec8d10f626e103389f3</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 16}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 84}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;QUEEN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A Queen is a female bee that lays eggs and is a crucial part of a Nucleus Hive (nuc)."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-eec9462a5adf7ec8d10f626e103389f3</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 16}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 84}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BROOD&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Brood refers to the developing larvae and pupae within a Nucleus Hive (nuc)."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-eec9462a5adf7ec8d10f626e103389f3</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 16}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 84}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HIVE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A Hive is a structure used by beekeepers to house bees, consisting of multiple parts that can be disassembled and reassembled."&lt;SEP&gt;"A Hive is the living space for a Nucleus Hive (nuc) where the bees live and work."&lt;SEP&gt;"A hive is a structure where bees live and produce honey, often managed by a beekeeper. Hives can contain multiple seasons of bee colonies and are sold for beekeeping purposes."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hive is a structure used to house bee colonies, providing shelter and space for the bees to live and produce honey."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6e8e292472440147bfd5caa5df68f872&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eec9462a5adf7ec8d10f626e103389f3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-81d8f3536901385c8434061c5fd290b6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8a0440abecaaae00e67c5e840094ac81</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 12}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 73}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 126}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FRAMES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Frames are components of a beehive that hold comb and honey within the boxes."&lt;SEP&gt;"Frames are the movable parts within the hive bodies and supers that hold the comb and honey."&lt;SEP&gt;"Frames are the structures within a Hive that hold comb, brood, and stored honey and pollen in a Nucleus Hive (nuc)."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-eec9462a5adf7ec8d10f626e103389f3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7b9cfa85a9917b7e3e3663f39bc8090b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b0630edb5f2e5f736478f6d764392a08</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 16}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 84}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;POLLEN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"MATERIAL"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Pollen is a food source for bees and is stored in the frames of a Nucleus Hive (nuc)."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-eec9462a5adf7ec8d10f626e103389f3</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 16}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 84}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HONEY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"MATERIAL"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Honey is a food source for bees and is stored in the frames of a Nucleus Hive (nuc)."&lt;SEP&gt;"Honey is the sweet substance produced by bees from flower nectar, stored in the hives for consumption and harvesting."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-eec9462a5adf7ec8d10f626e103389f3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b0630edb5f2e5f736478f6d764392a08</data>
