</node>
<node id="&quot;ADULT BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Adult Bees are the worker bees in a Nucleus Hive (nuc) that perform various tasks such as foraging, nursing, and maintaining the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-eec9462a5adf7ec8d10f626e103389f3</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 16}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 84}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COLONY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A Colony is the group of bees in a Nucleus Hive (nuc) that work together to maintain the hive and produce honey and pollen."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-eec9462a5adf7ec8d10f626e103389f3</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 16}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 84}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PROBLEM&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A Problem occurs occasionally when a queen is not accepted by the existing bees in the hive, causing issues with the integration of the Nucleus Hive (nuc)."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-eec9462a5adf7ec8d10f626e103389f3</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 16}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 84}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INSTALLATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Installation refers to the process of setting up a Nucleus Hive (nuc) in a hive, including the installation of the package and the queen."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-eec9462a5adf7ec8d10f626e103389f3</data>
