<node id="&quot;ESTABLISHED COLONY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"An established colony is a bee colony that has been in existence for at least one season, typically housed in two hive bodies or more, and contains a relatively large number of bees. Such a colony can be impressive but may be challenging for novices to handle effectively."&lt;SEP&gt;"Established Colony is a bee colony that has been in existence for at least one season, usually housed in multiple hive bodies and containing a large number of bees."</data>
