<node id="&quot;PANTOMIME&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Pantomime is a form of entertainment that involves silent mime and exaggerated gestures, contributing to the variety seen in American musical theater."&lt;SEP&gt;"Pantomime is a form of storytelling using body or facial movements, often paired with other types of entertainment, especially in the 1700s on the London and Broadway stages."&lt;SEP&gt;"Pantomime is a type of entertainment prevalent in the early era of American musical theater, contributing to its evolution."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-3709239da6185d654ded1afe4e373121&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-41335195b13ad0268bb37014c08227ef&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
