</node>
<node id="&quot;BURLESQUE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Burlesque is a form of entertainment that was popular before the rise of musical comedy, characterized by a more intimate style than pantomime and less childish than pantomime."&lt;SEP&gt;"Burlesque was a form of entertainment that combined comedy, satire, and sometimes nudity, influencing the comedic and sometimes risqué elements in American musical theater."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-41335195b13ad0268bb37014c08227ef&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 25}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MUSICAL COMEDY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Musical Comedy is a form of entertainment that emerged after the decline of pantomime, offering a more intimate style than burlesque and a less childish experience than pantomime."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-41335195b13ad0268bb37014c08227ef</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 25}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LONDON&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
