</node>
<node id="&quot;UNIVERSITIES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Universities are institutions of higher learning that are beginning to incorporate a historical thread or timeline into music classes."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f78a750cb7a4af5093bc7229882bc6f0</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 19}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TWENTY-YEAR-OLD&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A twenty-year-old individual is mentioned as someone who might not naturally connect music history issues to the music."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f78a750cb7a4af5093bc7229882bc6f0</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MUSIC THEATER EDUCATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Music theater education is an educational process focused on teaching the techniques and history of music theater."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f78a750cb7a4af5093bc7229882bc6f0</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 19}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FEMALE MUSIC THEATER MIX/BELT VOICE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Female music theater mix/belt voice is a vocal technique that emerged in the early nineteenth century and is considered an American vocal technique."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f78a750cb7a4af5093bc7229882bc6f0</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MIX/BELT SINGING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Mix/belt singing is a vocal technique that is more speech-oriented and allows female voices to project unamplified in the middle register."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f78a750cb7a4af5093bc7229882bc6f0</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FEMALE SPEAKING VOICE RANGE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Female speaking voice range is the vocal range that coincides with the female speaking voice, which mix/belt singing aims to project without amplification."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f78a750cb7a4af5093bc7229882bc6f0</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BELT SOUND&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Belt sound refers to the dominant vocal style used for females in musicals during the 1980s and 1990s."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f78a750cb7a4af5093bc7229882bc6f0</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;POP/ROCK STYLE MUSICAL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Pop/rock style musical is a type of musical that became popular in recent years and influenced the emergence of the 'legit' singing style."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f78a750cb7a4af5093bc7229882bc6f0</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LEGIT STYLE OF SINGING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Legit style of singing is a singing technique that is not part of the pop/rock singing style and emphasizes the use of the mix/belt singing voice."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f78a750cb7a4af5093bc7229882bc6f0</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EIGHTEENTH AND NINETEENTH CENTURIES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TIME PERIOD"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Eighteenth and nineteenth centuries refer to the historical periods during which the earliest American musicals were derived."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f78a750cb7a4af5093bc7229882bc6f0</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GREEN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Green is an author who wrote about the history of music theater, specifically mentioning the emergence of the female music theater mix/belt voice in the early nineteenth century."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f78a750cb7a4af5093bc7229882bc6f0</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ROLL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Roll is an author who wrote about the history and evolution of music theater singing styles, including mix/belt singing and the pop/rock style musicals."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f78a750cb7a4af5093bc7229882bc6f0</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;POP/ROCK STYLE MUSICALS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Pop/rock style musicals are a type of musical that became popular in recent years and influenced the emergence of the 'legit' singing style."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f78a750cb7a4af5093bc7229882bc6f0</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EIGHTEENTH CENTURY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TIME PERIOD"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The eighteenth century is a historical period during which the earliest American musicals were derived, indicating their origins."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f78a750cb7a4af5093bc7229882bc6f0</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NINETEENTH CENTURY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TIME PERIOD"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The nineteenth century is a historical period during which the earliest American musicals were derived, indicating their origins."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f78a750cb7a4af5093bc7229882bc6f0</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MIDDLE REGISTER (C4–C5)&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Middle register (C4–C5) is the vocal range that mix/belt singing aims to project unamplified, coinciding with the female speaking voice range."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f78a750cb7a4af5093bc7229882bc6f0</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HISTORICAL THREAD OR TIMELINE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Historical thread or timeline is an educational component being added to music classes to help students connect music history issues to the music."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f78a750cb7a4af5093bc7229882bc6f0</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 19}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ROLL, 2012&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Roll, 2012 refers to a publication or study that reported on the musical styles of Broadway shows in 2012, noting a significant number of pop/rock musicals."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 10}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 66}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 121}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;AMERICAN MUSICAL THEATER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"American Musical Theater is a form of theatrical performance that combines songs, spoken dialogue, acting, and dance, evolving from various European ancestral forms."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 24}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;OPERA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Opera is an early European form that influenced American musical theater, characterized by sung texts and typically staged with elaborate costumes and scenery."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 24}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;OPERETTA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Operetta is another European form that contributed to the development of American musical theater, featuring lighter and more comedic elements compared to opera."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 24}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EXTRAVAGANZA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Extravaganza is a form of entertainment that featured elaborate and often fantastical productions, influencing the grandiose nature of some American musicals."&lt;SEP&gt;"Extravaganza is a type of entertainment prevalent in the early era of American musical theater, contributing to its evolution."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3709239da6185d654ded1afe4e373121</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 20}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MINSTREL SHOW&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Minstrel Show is a type of entertainment prevalent in the early era of American musical theater, contributing to its evolution."&lt;SEP&gt;"Minstrel shows were a form of entertainment that used blackface performances, influencing the development of American musical theater, especially in terms of racial representation."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3709239da6185d654ded1afe4e373121</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 24}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VARIETY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Variety is a type of entertainment prevalent in the early era of American musical theater, contributing to its evolution."&lt;SEP&gt;"Variety shows were a form of entertainment that featured a wide range of acts, contributing to the diverse nature of American musical theater."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3709239da6185d654ded1afe4e373121</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 24}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;POP/ROCK&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Pop/Rock is a modern musical style that became prevalent in American musical theater, especially on Broadway, during the 2012 period."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 24}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MULTIETHNIC POPULATION SHIFTS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Multiethnic population shifts refer to the changing demographics of the United States, which have influenced the diversity in music theater styles and themes."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 24}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EUROPEAN FORMS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"European forms include opera, operetta, vaudeville, extravaganza, variety, burlesque, and minstrel shows, which have historically influenced American musical theater."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 24}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;AMERICAN MUSICAL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"American Musical refers to the unique form of theatrical performance that developed in the United States, blending various European and modern styles."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 24}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;1735–1864&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The period from 1735 to 1864 is marked by the early pioneers of American musical theater, including forms like extravaganza, pantomime, variety, and minstrel shows."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 20}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LUBBOCK, 1962&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Lubbock, 1962 refers to a publication or study that explored the historical connections between music theater and its European roots, as well as the gradual growth of the American musical."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;1864&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"1864 marks the end of the early pioneers period in American musical theater, signaling a transition in the development of the genre."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 20}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MODERN INNOVATIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Modern innovations in music theater have given rise to current singing and styles, building upon the foundations laid by earlier forms."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CURRENT MUSIC THEATER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Current music theater refers to the contemporary form of theatrical performance that continues to evolve and incorporate various styles and innovations."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EUROPEAN ROOTS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"European roots include opera, operetta, vaudeville, extravaganza, variety, burlesque, and minstrel shows, which have historically influenced American musical theater."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GRADUAL GROWTH&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Gradual growth refers to the process by which the American musical developed its own identity over time, rather than simply mimicking European forms."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;THEATERS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Theaters are venues where musicals and other theatrical performances take place, contributing to the evolution of music theater in America."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;THEATER DISTRICT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Theater district is a specific area within a city where theaters and other performance venues are concentrated, such as Broadway in New York City."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;UNITED STATES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The United States is the country where American musical theater developed and evolved over time, influenced by its diverse population."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DIVERSE NATURE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Diverse nature refers to the variety of styles and themes found in American musical theater, reflecting the multiethnic population of the United States."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RACIAL REPRESENTATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Racial representation refers to the depiction of different racial groups in American musical theater, influenced by forms like minstrel shows."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SATIRE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Satire is a form of humor that uses irony, ridicule, and criticism to expose and comment on vices, follies, abuses, and shortcomings, influencing the development of American musical theater."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NUDITY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Nudity is a controversial element that has been part of some forms of entertainment, such as burlesque, influencing the development of American musical theater."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Dance is a crucial component of music theater, often integrated with singing and spoken dialogue to enhance the storytelling and emotional impact."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COSTUMES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Costumes are an important aspect of music theater, helping to define characters and settings, as seen in elaborate productions like extravaganza."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SCENERY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Scenery is a key element in music theater, creating visual environments that support the narrative and enhance the overall production."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DIALOGUE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Dialogue is a vital part of music theater, combining with singing and dance to tell the story and develop characters."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ACTING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Acting is essential in music theater, bringing characters to life and driving the narrative forward."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MODERN STYLES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Modern styles include pop, rock, rhythm and blues, and jazz, which have become integral to the development of American musical theater."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MULTIETHNIC POPULATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Multiethnic population refers to the diverse demographic makeup of the United States, influencing the themes and styles of American musical theater."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GRANDIOSE NATURE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Grandiose nature refers to the elaborate and often fantastical productions that have characterized some American musicals, influenced by forms like extravaganza."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RHYTHMIC PATTERNS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Rhythmic patterns are an important aspect of music theater, contributing to the musicality and pacing of performances."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ELABORATE COSTUMES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Elaborate costumes are a key feature of music theater, enhancing the visual appeal and character development of productions."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ELABORATE PRODUCTIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Elaborate productions are a hallmark of music theater, often involving complex sets, costumes, and choreography."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COMPLEX SETS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Complex sets are an important aspect of music theater, creating immersive environments that support the narrative and enhance the overall production."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CHOREOGRAPHY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Choreography is a crucial component of music theater, integrating dance with singing and spoken dialogue to create a cohesive performance."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NARRATIVE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Narrative is the core of music theater, telling stories through a combination of singing, dialogue, and dance."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EMOTIONAL IMPACT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Emotional impact is a key goal of music theater, aiming to move and engage audiences through powerful performances."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;POWERFUL PERFORMANCES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Powerful performances are a hallmark of music theater, designed to captivate and emotionally connect with audiences."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;AUDIENCES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Audiences are the people who attend music theater performances, experiencing the stories and emotions conveyed through the production."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PERFORMANCES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Performances are the live presentations of music theater, combining singing, dialogue, and dance to tell stories and entertain audiences."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LIVE PRESENTATIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Live presentations are a defining characteristic of music theater, distinguishing it from other forms of entertainment."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ENTERTAINMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Entertainment is the primary purpose of music theater, providing enjoyment and engagement for audiences through performances."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ENJOYMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Enjoyment is a key outcome of music theater, designed to entertain and engage audiences through compelling performances."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ENGAGEMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Engagement is a goal of music theater, aiming to draw audiences into the stories and emotions conveyed through the production."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COMPELLING PERFORMANCES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Compelling performances are a hallmark of music theater, designed to captivate and emotionally connect with audiences."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-289a23908915c5bcd0308dffe4b44213</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;STORIES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
