</node>
<node id="&quot;OUTER COVER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Outer cover is a component of a beehive that protects the uppermost box from the elements."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b0630edb5f2e5f736478f6d764392a08</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 16}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 85}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 136}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INNER COVER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Inner cover is a component of a beehive placed between the top super and the outer cover to provide space for the bees."&lt;SEP&gt;"Inner cover is a component placed inside the hive to separate the uppermost box from the rest of the hive contents."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7b9cfa85a9917b7e3e3663f39bc8090b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b0630edb5f2e5f736478f6d764392a08</data>
