</node>
<node id="&quot;SUPERS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Supers are additional boxes added above the hive body to increase storage capacity for honey."&lt;SEP&gt;"Supers are additional boxes placed above the hive bodies to provide more space for the bees to store honey and raise brood."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7b9cfa85a9917b7e3e3663f39bc8090b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b0630edb5f2e5f736478f6d764392a08</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 16}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 85}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 136}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Bees are managed by beekeepers and are crucial for pollination and honey production."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees are not present on the island, adding to the sparse insect population."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees are the focus of Cannon's discussion on how different animals interact with them, particularly in terms of space and proximity."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees are the insects housed in the hive."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees are the primary focus of hive management and care, ensuring the health and productivity of the colony."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees are the primary inhabitants of the beehive, responsible for producing honey and maintaining the colony."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bees are the primary users of hive bodies and supers, and are sensitive to various internal conditions."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2627e4a21f651e709836d7ce2b93ce75&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7b9cfa85a9917b7e3e3663f39bc8090b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b0630edb5f2e5f736478f6d764392a08&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-06b4a9642d883a25a7c071da2debc224&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1967e91acf93914bfc451b9362900ea1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3d1f018f894ed3aab36e02fad8d45d76&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-81d8f3536901385c8434061c5fd290b6</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 18}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 89}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 143}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WEATHER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Weather conditions such as temperature and sunlight affect the hive environment and the choice of paint color."&lt;SEP&gt;"Weather conditions, such as temperature and precipitation, affect the longevity and maintenance of beehives."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7b9cfa85a9917b7e3e3663f39bc8090b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b0630edb5f2e5f736478f6d764392a08</data>
