  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Hive bodies and supers refer to the structures used by bees to house their colonies, which are essential for beekeeping operations."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-06b4a9642d883a25a7c071da2debc224</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;THE HIVE STAND&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The hive stand is a piece of equipment used to support the hive, keeping the wooden bottom board off the ground to prevent dampness and rot."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-06b4a9642d883a25a7c071da2debc224</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DAMPNESS AND ROT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Dampness and rot are conditions that can damage the hive stand and bottom board, necessitating proper support and maintenance."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-06b4a9642d883a25a7c071da2debc224</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BLOOD PH&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Blood pH is a measure of the acidity or alkalinity of the blood, which is maintained near 7.4 for optimal health."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-06b4a9642d883a25a7c071da2debc224</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COMA AND DEATH&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Coma and death are severe medical conditions that can result from a drop in blood pH below 6.95."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-06b4a9642d883a25a7c071da2debc224</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CONVULSIONS AND SEIZURES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Convulsions and seizures are symptoms that can occur when blood pH rises above 7.7."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-06b4a9642d883a25a7c071da2debc224</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CALCIUM LEVELS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Calcium levels are maintained around 10 milligrams per 100 milliliters of blood, with levels below or above this range causing serious health issues."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-06b4a9642d883a25a7c071da2debc224</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WOODEN BOTTOM BOARD&quot;">
