<node id="&quot;OSCILLATIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Oscillations are variations in internal conditions that the nervous and endocrine systems aim to prevent."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-06b4a9642d883a25a7c071da2debc224</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SERIOUS ILLNESS OR DEATH&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Serious illness or death are outcomes of breaching the narrow limits of internal conditions."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-06b4a9642d883a25a7c071da2debc224</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WALTER B. CANNON&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Walter B. Cannon was a prominent figure in the field of physiology, known for his work on the 'wisdom of the body' and the role of insulin in blood sugar regulation."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-529cfcb3c05c829427368393e6f20532</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 35}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 99}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BLOOD SUGAR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Blood Sugar refers to the concentration of glucose in the blood, which is regulated by various physiological mechanisms."&lt;SEP&gt;"Blood sugar is another example of a state regulated by opposing factors."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-3d1f018f894ed3aab36e02fad8d45d76&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-529cfcb3c05c829427368393e6f20532</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 38}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VAGUS NERVES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Vagus Nerves are part of the autonomic nervous system that stimulate the pancreas to release insulin when blood sugar levels rise."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-529cfcb3c05c829427368393e6f20532</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 35}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 99}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ADRENAL GLANDS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Adrenal Glands are responsible for releasing sugar from the liver when blood sugar levels fall, maintaining homeostasis."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-529cfcb3c05c829427368393e6f20532</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 35}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 99}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PANCREAS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGAN"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The Pancreas is an organ that secretes insulin in response to rising blood sugar levels, helping to regulate blood sugar."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-529cfcb3c05c829427368393e6f20532</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 35}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 99}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LIVER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGAN"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The Liver stores and releases sugar in response to falling blood sugar levels, contributing to the maintenance of blood sugar levels."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-529cfcb3c05c829427368393e6f20532</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 35}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 99}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ADAPTIVE MECHANISMS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Adaptive Mechanisms refer to the body's ability to maintain homeostasis through various physiological responses to changes in blood sugar levels."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-529cfcb3c05c829427368393e6f20532</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 35}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 99}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CONVULSIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Convulsions are severe muscle contractions that can occur due to low or high levels of certain substances in the blood, such as calcium or blood sugar."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-529cfcb3c05c829427368393e6f20532</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SEIZURES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Seizures are a result of abnormal electrical activity in the brain, which can be triggered by various factors including changes in blood sugar levels."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-529cfcb3c05c829427368393e6f20532</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CALCIUM&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"SUBSTANCE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Calcium is a mineral essential for various bodily functions, including nerve and muscle function, and its levels must be maintained within a specific range to avoid health issues like convulsions."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-529cfcb3c05c829427368393e6f20532</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 38}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SUGAR LEVELS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Sugar Levels refer to the concentration of glucose in the blood, which must be regulated to prevent conditions like convulsions and seizures."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-529cfcb3c05c829427368393e6f20532</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;AUTONOMIC NERVOUS SYSTEM&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"SYSTEM"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The Autonomic Nervous System controls involuntary actions such as heart rate, digestion, respiratory rate, and the diameter of blood vessels, playing a crucial role in maintaining homeostasis."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-529cfcb3c05c829427368393e6f20532</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 34}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ADRENALS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGAN"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The Adrenals are a pair of endocrine glands located on top of the kidneys that produce hormones such as adrenaline and cortisol, which help in responding to stress and regulating blood sugar levels."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-529cfcb3c05c829427368393e6f20532</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 38}]</data>
</node>
