  <data key="d6">chunk-16d39b19193e67d1a3c47d1a2851f964</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VOCAL FOLD VIBRATION&quot;" target="&quot;MODE 1&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Mode 1 of vocal fold vibration produces a brighter, brassier sound due to its strong high-frequency harmonics."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-16d39b19193e67d1a3c47d1a2851f964</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VOCAL FOLD VIBRATION&quot;" target="&quot;MODE 2&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Mode 2 of vocal fold vibration produces a less bright sound due to its weak high-frequency harmonics."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-16d39b19193e67d1a3c47d1a2851f964</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VOCAL TRACT&quot;" target="&quot;RESONANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">26.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The vocal tract plays a crucial role in the phenomenon of resonance, where it synchronizes with the sound source to amplify sound."&lt;SEP&gt;"The vocal tract serves as the source of resonance, amplifying and enhancing the sound through supplemental vibration."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-19cc232c450902b9e868c6fdfd3aa6b0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-16d39b19193e67d1a3c47d1a2851f964</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VOCAL TRACT&quot;" target="&quot;FREE RESONANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Free Resonance occurs when sound travels through the Vocal Tract, creating echoes that enhance the quality of sound."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-0693f03528085d6f9c9b9a9f1da30c13</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;RESONANCE&quot;" target="&quot;SUPPLEMENTAL VIBRATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">27.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Resonance enhances the original vibrations of the sound source through supplemental vibration, making the sound louder and more beautiful."&lt;SEP&gt;"Resonance enhances the original vibrations of the sound source through supplemental vibration."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-16d39b19193e67d1a3c47d1a2851f964</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;RESONANCE&quot;" target="&quot;AMPLIFICATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Resonance amplifies the sound by enhancing the original vibrations."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-16d39b19193e67d1a3c47d1a2851f964</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;RESONANCE&quot;" target="&quot;ENHANCEMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Resonance enriches the sound by enhancing the original vibrations."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-16d39b19193e67d1a3c47d1a2851f964</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;RESONANCE&quot;" target="&quot;FREE RESONANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Resonance can occur through free vibration without physical connection to a vibrator."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-16d39b19193e67d1a3c47d1a2851f964</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;RESONANCE&quot;" target="&quot;FORCED RESONANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Resonance can occur through forced vibration with physical connection to a vibrator."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-16d39b19193e67d1a3c47d1a2851f964</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;RESONANCE&quot;" target="&quot;GLOTTIS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The glottis is involved in the synchronization process during resonance, contributing to the amplification of sound."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-19cc232c450902b9e868c6fdfd3aa6b0</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;RESONANCE&quot;" target="&quot;SOUND&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Sound is the element that is amplified through the process of resonance in the vocal tract."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-19cc232c450902b9e868c6fdfd3aa6b0</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;RESONANCE&quot;" target="&quot;CANYON&quot;">
  <data key="d4">12.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The concept of a canyon is used to illustrate the reflection of sound waves, similar to how sound reflects in the vocal tract during resonance."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-19cc232c450902b9e868c6fdfd3aa6b0</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;RESONANCE&quot;" target="&quot;FORMANTS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Formants are the specific frequencies at which resonance occurs, providing areas of strong amplification in the vocal tract."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-19cc232c450902b9e868c6fdfd3aa6b0</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SOUNDBOARD&quot;" target="&quot;BRIDGE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">24.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Bridge and Soundboard work together to amplify sound."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Soundboard and Bridge work together to transmit vibrations from the strings, amplifying the sound produced by the instrument."&lt;SEP&gt;"The soundboard in pianos is amplified by the bridge, which transmits the vibrations of the strings."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-0693f03528085d6f9c9b9a9f1da30c13&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-16d39b19193e67d1a3c47d1a2851f964</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SOUNDBOARD&quot;" target="&quot;PIANO&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Piano uses a soundboard to amplify the vibrations of the strings."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-16d39b19193e67d1a3c47d1a2851f964</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SOUNDBOARD&quot;" target="&quot;VIOLIN&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Violin uses a soundboard to amplify the vibrations of the strings."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-16d39b19193e67d1a3c47d1a2851f964</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SOUNDBOARD&quot;" target="&quot;GUITAR&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Guitar uses a soundboard to amplify the vibrations of the strings."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-16d39b19193e67d1a3c47d1a2851f964</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BRIDGE&quot;" target="&quot;STRINGS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">17.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Strings transmit vibrations to the Bridge."&lt;SEP&gt;"The bridge in pianos, violins, and guitars transmits the vibrations of the strings to the soundboard."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-0693f03528085d6f9c9b9a9f1da30c13&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-16d39b19193e67d1a3c47d1a2851f964</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BRIDGE&quot;" target="&quot;PIANO&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Piano uses a bridge to transmit the vibrations of the strings to the soundboard."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-16d39b19193e67d1a3c47d1a2851f964</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BRIDGE&quot;" target="&quot;VIOLIN&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Violin uses a bridge to transmit the vibrations of the strings to the soundboard."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-16d39b19193e67d1a3c47d1a2851f964</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BRIDGE&quot;" target="&quot;GUITAR&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Guitar uses a bridge to transmit the vibrations of the strings to the soundboard."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-16d39b19193e67d1a3c47d1a2851f964</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;TONES&quot;" target="&quot;HIGH-FREQUENCY HARMONICS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"High-frequency harmonics are individual tones produced by the vocal folds in Mode 1."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-16d39b19193e67d1a3c47d1a2851f964</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HIGH-FREQUENCY HARMONICS&quot;" target="&quot;BRIGHTER SOUND&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Brighter Sound is the result of strong high-frequency harmonics in Mode 1."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-16d39b19193e67d1a3c47d1a2851f964</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;AMPLIFICATION&quot;" target="&quot;MULLIGAN GUARD&quot;">
  <data key="d4">12.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Amplification technology was not yet available during the time of the Mulligan Guard series, but it influenced later productions."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-026ac83dff25b4f662d33b415113ce9e</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;AMPLIFICATION&quot;" target="&quot;MIX/BELT SINGING&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Mix/belt singing aims to avoid amplification in the middle register (C4–C5), emphasizing its natural projection capabilities."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-f78a750cb7a4af5093bc7229882bc6f0</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;INSTRUMENTS&quot;" target="&quot;PIANO&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Piano is an example of an instrument that uses strings and a soundboard to produce sound."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-16d39b19193e67d1a3c47d1a2851f964</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;INSTRUMENTS&quot;" target="&quot;VIOLIN&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Violin is an example of an instrument that uses strings and a soundboard to produce sound."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-16d39b19193e67d1a3c47d1a2851f964</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;INSTRUMENTS&quot;" target="&quot;GUITAR&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Guitar is an example of an instrument that uses strings and a soundboard to produce sound."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-16d39b19193e67d1a3c47d1a2851f964</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PIANO&quot;" target="&quot;STRINGS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Piano uses strings to produce sound."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-16d39b19193e67d1a3c47d1a2851f964</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VIOLIN&quot;" target="&quot;STRINGS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Violin uses strings to produce sound."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-16d39b19193e67d1a3c47d1a2851f964</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;GUITAR&quot;" target="&quot;STRINGS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Guitar uses strings to produce sound."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-16d39b19193e67d1a3c47d1a2851f964</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;STRINGS&quot;" target="&quot;VIBRATIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">28.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Strings vibrate to produce sound."&lt;SEP&gt;"Vibrations in the Strings produce sound."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-0693f03528085d6f9c9b9a9f1da30c13&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-16d39b19193e67d1a3c47d1a2851f964</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;STRINGS&quot;" target="&quot;BOARD&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Board transmits vibrations from the Strings."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-0693f03528085d6f9c9b9a9f1da30c13</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;FORCED RESONANCE&quot;" target="&quot;VOCAL FOLDS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Forced Resonance involves vibrations transmitted through the chest, impacting the self-perception of sound without being audible to others."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-0693f03528085d6f9c9b9a9f1da30c13</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VIBRATIONS&quot;" target="&quot;AIR COLUMN&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Air columns vibrate to produce sound, as in flutes and organs."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-16d39b19193e67d1a3c47d1a2851f964</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VIBRATIONS&quot;" target="&quot;VOCAL FOLDS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">20.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Vibrations in the Vocal Folds produce sound."&lt;SEP&gt;"Vibrations in the vocal folds are responsible for producing sound during speech and singing."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-0693f03528085d6f9c9b9a9f1da30c13</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VIBRATIONS&quot;" target="&quot;CHEST&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Vibrations can be felt in the Chest during speech."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-0693f03528085d6f9c9b9a9f1da30c13</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VIBRATIONS&quot;" target="&quot;PHARYNX&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Vibrations travel through the Pharynx."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-0693f03528085d6f9c9b9a9f1da30c13</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VIBRATIONS&quot;" target="&quot;ORAL CAVITY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Vibrations travel through the Oral Cavity."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-0693f03528085d6f9c9b9a9f1da30c13</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VIBRATIONS&quot;" target="&quot;NASAL CAVITY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Vibrations travel through the Nasal Cavity."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-0693f03528085d6f9c9b9a9f1da30c13</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VIBRATIONS&quot;" target="&quot;GLOTTIS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Vibrations are emitted from the Glottis."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-0693f03528085d6f9c9b9a9f1da30c13</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VIBRATIONS&quot;" target="&quot;TRUMPET&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Vibrations travel through the Trumpet."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-0693f03528085d6f9c9b9a9f1da30c13</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VIBRATIONS&quot;" target="&quot;ORGAN PIPE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Vibrations travel through the Organ Pipe."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-0693f03528085d6f9c9b9a9f1da30c13</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VIBRATIONS&quot;" target="&quot;ECHOES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Complex patterns of Echoes are created in the Vocal Tract."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-0693f03528085d6f9c9b9a9f1da30c13</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;GLOTTIS&quot;" target="&quot;VOCAL FOLDS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Glottis is the opening where the Vocal Folds are located, essential for producing sound."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-0693f03528085d6f9c9b9a9f1da30c13</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;GLOTTIS&quot;" target="&quot;ECHOES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Echoes arrive back at the Glottis at the precise moment a new Pulse of Sound is created."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-0693f03528085d6f9c9b9a9f1da30c13</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;EXPENSE REIMBURSEMENT AMOUNT&quot;" target="&quot;EXIT FACILITY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Expense Reimbursement Amount is related to the Exit Facility, as it involves costs associated with the authorization and preparation for the transaction."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-19cc232c450902b9e868c6fdfd3aa6b0</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
