<edge source="&quot;NUCLEUS HIVE (NUC)&quot;" target="&quot;ESTABLISHED HIVE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">32.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"A Nucleus Hive (nuc) is drawn from an established hive, inheriting its components such as frames, comb, brood, adult bees, and a new, young queen."&lt;SEP&gt;"An Established Hive provides the source of bees, frames, comb, brood, and a queen for a Nucleus Hive (nuc)."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-eec9462a5adf7ec8d10f626e103389f3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NUCLEUS HIVE (NUC)&quot;" target="&quot;NEW BEEKEEPER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">70.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"A New Beekeeper purchases and uses a Nucleus Hive (nuc) as a starter unit for their beekeeping operation."&lt;SEP&gt;"A Nucleus Hive (nuc) is purchased and used by a new beekeeper to establish their beekeeping colony."&lt;SEP&gt;"A Nucleus Hive (nuc) is purchased and used by a new beekeeper to start their beekeeping operation."&lt;SEP&gt;"A new beekeeper acquires and uses a Nucleus Hive (nuc) to establish their beekeeping colony."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-eec9462a5adf7ec8d10f626e103389f3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NUCLEUS HIVE (NUC)&quot;" target="&quot;THROW-AWAY BOX&quot;">
  <data key="d4">24.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"A Nucleus Hive (nuc) is sometimes housed in a throw-away box before being transferred to a permanent hive."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-eec9462a5adf7ec8d10f626e103389f3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NUCLEUS HIVE (NUC)&quot;" target="&quot;RETURNABLE BOX&quot;">
  <data key="d4">28.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"A Nucleus Hive (nuc) is sometimes transported in a returnable box to its new home."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-eec9462a5adf7ec8d10f626e103389f3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NUCLEUS HIVE (NUC)&quot;" target="&quot;SINGLE-STORY HIVE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">24.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"A Nucleus Hive (nuc) might be carried home in a single-story hive structure by a new beekeeper."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-eec9462a5adf7ec8d10f626e103389f3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NUCLEUS HIVE (NUC)&quot;" target="&quot;PACKAGE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"A Package is a component of a Nucleus Hive (nuc) that is installed in the hive before the colony is fully accepted by the existing bees."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-eec9462a5adf7ec8d10f626e103389f3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NUCLEUS HIVE (NUC)&quot;" target="&quot;QUEEN&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"A Queen is a crucial part of a Nucleus Hive (nuc) that lays eggs and helps integrate the new colony into the existing hive."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-eec9462a5adf7ec8d10f626e103389f3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NUCLEUS HIVE (NUC)&quot;" target="&quot;BROOD&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Brood refers to the developing larvae and pupae within a Nucleus Hive (nuc), which are cared for by the adult bees."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-eec9462a5adf7ec8d10f626e103389f3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NUCLEUS HIVE (NUC)&quot;" target="&quot;HIVE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"A Hive is the living space for a Nucleus Hive (nuc) where the bees live and work, integrating the new colony into the existing hive structure."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-eec9462a5adf7ec8d10f626e103389f3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NUCLEUS HIVE (NUC)&quot;" target="&quot;FRAMES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Frames are the structures within a Hive that hold comb, brood, and stored honey and pollen in a Nucleus Hive (nuc), providing essential resources for the colony."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-eec9462a5adf7ec8d10f626e103389f3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NUCLEUS HIVE (NUC)&quot;" target="&quot;POLLEN&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Pollen is a food source for bees and is stored in the frames of a Nucleus Hive (nuc), supporting the colony's nutrition needs."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-eec9462a5adf7ec8d10f626e103389f3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NUCLEUS HIVE (NUC)&quot;" target="&quot;HONEY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Honey is a food source for bees and is stored in the frames of a Nucleus Hive (nuc), supporting the colony's nutrition needs."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-eec9462a5adf7ec8d10f626e103389f3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NUCLEUS HIVE (NUC)&quot;" target="&quot;ADULT BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Adult Bees are the worker bees in a Nucleus Hive (nuc) that perform various tasks such as foraging, nursing, and maintaining the hive, ensuring the colony's survival and growth."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-eec9462a5adf7ec8d10f626e103389f3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NUCLEUS HIVE (NUC)&quot;" target="&quot;COLONY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"A Colony is the group of bees in a Nucleus Hive (nuc) that work together to maintain the hive and produce honey and pollen, forming a cohesive unit within the larger hive structure."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-eec9462a5adf7ec8d10f626e103389f3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NUCLEUS HIVE (NUC)&quot;" target="&quot;PROBLEM&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"A Problem occurs occasionally when a queen is not accepted by the existing bees in the hive, causing issues with the integration of the Nucleus Hive (nuc)."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-eec9462a5adf7ec8d10f626e103389f3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NUCLEUS HIVE (NUC)&quot;" target="&quot;INSTALLATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Installation refers to the process of setting up a Nucleus Hive (nuc) in a hive, including the installation of the package and the queen, which is a critical step in the integration of the new colony."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-eec9462a5adf7ec8d10f626e103389f3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NEW BEEKEEPER&quot;" target="&quot;ESTABLISHED HIVE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">40.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"A New Beekeeper purchases a Nucleus Hive (nuc) from an Established Hive to start their beekeeping operation."&lt;SEP&gt;"A New Beekeeper purchases a Nucleus Hive (nuc) from an established hive, integrating it into their beekeeping operation."&lt;SEP&gt;"An Established Hive provides a source of bees, frames, comb, brood, and a queen for a new beekeeper who purchases a Nucleus Hive (nuc)."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-eec9462a5adf7ec8d10f626e103389f3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NEW BEEKEEPER&quot;" target="&quot;SINGLE-STORY HIVE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">19.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"A New Beekeeper might use a single-story hive to accept and transport a Nucleus Hive (nuc) to their new home."&lt;SEP&gt;"A new beekeeper might use a single-story hive to accept and transport a Nucleus Hive (nuc) to their new home."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-eec9462a5adf7ec8d10f626e103389f3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NEW BEEKEEPER&quot;" target="&quot;THROW-AWAY BOX&quot;">
  <data key="d4">24.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"A New Beekeeper might use a throw-away box to house a Nucleus Hive (nuc) temporarily before transferring it to a permanent hive."&lt;SEP&gt;"A new beekeeper might use a throw-away box to house a Nucleus Hive (nuc) temporarily before transferring it to a permanent hive."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-eec9462a5adf7ec8d10f626e103389f3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NEW BEEKEEPER&quot;" target="&quot;RETURNABLE BOX&quot;">
  <data key="d4">21.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"A New Beekeeper might use a returnable box to transport a Nucleus Hive (nuc) to their new home."&lt;SEP&gt;"A new beekeeper might use a returnable box to transport a Nucleus Hive (nuc) to their new home."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-eec9462a5adf7ec8d10f626e103389f3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NEW BEEKEEPER&quot;" target="&quot;NUC&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Nuc is suitable for new beekeepers due to its minimal defensiveness and ease of management."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-6e8e292472440147bfd5caa5df68f872</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
