  <data key="d4">153.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Beekeeping involves managing Hives, providing shelter and resources for the bees."&lt;SEP&gt;"Beekeeping involves managing hives, providing shelter and resources for the bees."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-6e8e292472440147bfd5caa5df68f872</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HIVE&quot;" target="&quot;NOVICE BEEKEEPER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Novice beekeepers may struggle to manage hives that are in poor condition, especially established colonies."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-8a0440abecaaae00e67c5e840094ac81</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HIVE&quot;" target="&quot;ESTABLISHED COLONY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">98.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"An established colony is typically housed in one or more hives, indicating a strong association between the two."&lt;SEP&gt;"Established colonies are often housed in hives that may be in poor condition, making them challenging for novices to manage."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hives can contain established colonies that may be in poor condition, affecting the beekeeper's ability to manage them."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-8a0440abecaaae00e67c5e840094ac81</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HIVE&quot;" target="&quot;NOVICE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Hives may be in poor condition due to neglect, making them challenging for novices to manage effectively."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-8a0440abecaaae00e67c5e840094ac81</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HIVE&quot;" target="&quot;SWARM&quot;">
  <data key="d4">134.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Hives can be sources of swarms, which are then captured to start new colonies, showing a continuous cycle in beekeeping."&lt;SEP&gt;"Swarms are often captured from hives that may be in poor condition, indicating a link between the two."&lt;SEP&gt;"Swarms are often captured to start new colonies, showing a direct link between the two."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-8a0440abecaaae00e67c5e840094ac81</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HIVE&quot;" target="&quot;BEEKEEPER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Beekeepers manage hives, including both established colonies and swarms."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-8a0440abecaaae00e67c5e840094ac81</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HIVE&quot;" target="&quot;PACKAGE BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Package bees are introduced to hives to start new colonies, often replacing established colonies."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-8a0440abecaaae00e67c5e840094ac81</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HIVE&quot;" target="&quot;EQUIPMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d4">6.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Equipment used in beekeeping can affect the condition of the hive, with proper equipment helping to maintain a healthy colony."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-8a0440abecaaae00e67c5e840094ac81</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HIVE&quot;" target="&quot;DISEASE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Disease can affect the health of the hive, leading to a decline in the population and overall colony strength."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-8a0440abecaaae00e67c5e840094ac81</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HIVE&quot;" target="&quot;DEFECTIVE EQUIPMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Defective equipment can harm the hive, leading to a decline in the population and overall colony strength."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-8a0440abecaaae00e67c5e840094ac81</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HIVE&quot;" target="&quot;DEBT&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Debt can cause hive owners to sell their hives, often resulting in hives being in poor condition."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-8a0440abecaaae00e67c5e840094ac81</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HIVE&quot;" target="&quot;AGE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The age of the hive can affect its condition, with older hives potentially being less healthy."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-8a0440abecaaae00e67c5e840094ac81</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HIVE&quot;" target="&quot;ILL HEALTH&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The ill health of the hive owner can lead to neglect, resulting in a decline in the condition of the hive."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-8a0440abecaaae00e67c5e840094ac81</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HIVE&quot;" target="&quot;HIVE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">36.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Hives can be in poor condition due to neglect, affecting the quality of the colony within, and this can be challenging for novices to recognize."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-8a0440abecaaae00e67c5e840094ac81</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HIVE&quot;" target="&quot;BEARS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">5.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bears are a special problem that needs to be considered when setting up a hive, though they do not directly interact with the hive."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-81d8f3536901385c8434061c5fd290b6</data>
