</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HIVE&quot;" target="&quot;LEVEL GROUND&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Level Ground is preferred for hive placement, preventing cool or moist air from pooling around the hive."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-81d8f3536901385c8434061c5fd290b6</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HIVE&quot;" target="&quot;GENTLE SLOPE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"A Gentle Slope is beneficial for hive placement, allowing cool or moist air to flow away from the hive."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-81d8f3536901385c8434061c5fd290b6</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HIVE&quot;" target="&quot;STEEP SLOPE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"A Steep Slope should be avoided for hive placement, as it can cause hive parts to slide down the hill."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-81d8f3536901385c8434061c5fd290b6</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HIVE&quot;" target="&quot;DEPRESSION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Depressions should be avoided for hive placement, as they can collect cool or moist air, which is undesirable."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-81d8f3536901385c8434061c5fd290b6</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
